## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of online resources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. The Gilded Age is a complex period with diverse perspectives, and the sources used may not fully capture all aspects of how traditional understandings of freedom were challenged. Additionally, the focus on economic and social aspects may overlook other cultural or political dimensions of the era.